<1ST_LINE>b p AM-DukakisWiner-Calif     06-08 0060</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Dukakis Winer-Calif,30</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>BULLETIN</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Michael Dukakis won the California
presidential primary Tuesday night and picked up more than enough
delegates to clinch a first-ballot nomination at the Democratic
National Convention. His victory completed a four-state sweep on the
final night of the 1988 primary campaign.
   Jesse Jackson finished second in each of the four states.
