<1ST_LINE>u p AM-OlympiaDukakis     06-08 0296</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Olympia Dukakis,310</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Curtain Falls On Delegate Bid By Actress Olympia Dukakis</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JO ASTRID GLADING</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEWARK, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Not every Dukakis was a winner in Tuesday's
New Jersey presidential primary: Academy Award-winning actress
Olympia Dukakis lost in her bid to be a delegate for her cousin
Michael at the Democratic National Convention.
   With 283 of the 286 precincts reporting in Ms. Dukakis' 18th
Delegate District in Essex County, Jesse Jackson had 26,222 votes to
22,175 votes for Michael Dukakis, according to unofficial returns.
   In the separate delegate election, the five delegate candidates
pledged to Jackson won, while Ms. Dukakis and the four other
candidates pledged to the Massachusetts governor lost.
   Robert Noonan, the husband of one of the district's Dukakis
delegates, Joanna Noonan, said the Dukakis delegate slate had
conceeded. ``Sure we're disappointed,'' he said.
   Brenda Neily, an official at Dukakis' campaign headquarters in
Boston, said Olympia's loss came as ``a disappointment, but not a
surprise.''
   The delegate district includes not only suburban, middle-class
Montclair, where Ms. Dukakis lives, but also inner-city areas in
Orange and East Orange.
   Michael Dukakis fared much better, winning the statewide primary
by a wide margin. With 97 percent of the precincts reporting, he had
65 percent of the vote to 31 percent for Jesse Jackson.
   Ms. Dukakis won the Academy Award this year for her role in the
movie ``Moonstruck'' and gave her cousin's campaign a plug when she
accepted the Oscar. ``OK, Michael, let's go!'' she yelled, waving
the statuette.
   In the weeks that followed, she made a number of campaign
appearances with the Massachusetts governor.
   Tuesday night, Ms. Dukakis was reported to be in Vancouver,
British Columbia, filming a movie, and could not be reached for
comment about the election results.
</TEXT>
