<1ST_LINE>r i PM-KremlinTreasure     06-08 0126</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Kremlin Treasure,0129</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Buried Treasure Unearthed Inside Kremlin</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Excavation workers unearthed gold, silver,
precious stones and other valuables buried inside the Kremlin walls
about 750 years ago, a weekly newspaper reported today.
   The buried treasure included pendants, rings, necklaces,
pendants and Slavonic decorations from the period, the Moscow News
reported.
   It said the riches were buried by defenders of the Kremlin to
protect the goods against the Mongolian invasion of 1237. They were
found on the Kremlin's Borovitsky Hill, which overlooks the Moscow
River.
   The Mongols controlled the Slavic regions of present-day Soviet
Union until the 14th century, exacting high taxes, conscripting the
male poulation and harshly repressing revolts.
   Moscow News said the value of the treasure had not yet been
assessed.
</TEXT>
