<HEAD>London Bookmaker Makes Dukakis Favorite In U.S. Election</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ladbroke's, one of London's leading bookmakers,
today made Democrat Michael Dukakis the favorite to beat Republican
George Bush in the U.S. presidential election in November.
   Ladbroke's made Dukakis the 8-11 favorite, which means if you
bet $11 and Dukakis wins, you get $8 plus your original stake. Bush
was given even odds, which means if you bet $1, you win a dollar
and get back your $1 stake.
   The Massachusetts governor on Tuesday won Democratic primaries
in California, Montana, New Jersey and New Mexico and has more than
enough committed delegates to win the party's nomination for
president.
</TEXT>
