<HEAD>Nicaragua Calls Off Search For Missing Plane</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANAGUA, Nicaragua (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The government called off the search
for a cargo plane with six people aboard that was reported missing
15 days ago.
   ``There is nothing more to do. We have searched in all areas
where the plane could have possibly fallen,'' Oscar Melendez, the
deputy minister for transportation and construction said at a news
conference Tuesday.
   The DC-6 cargo plane, operated by the government-run Aeronica
company, disappeared May 24 en route to Managua from Panama on a
routine supply run. The last word from the crew came 1{ hours after
takeoff in a radio message that said ``all is normal,'' according
to the newspaper El Nuevo Diario.
   A search began shortly after the plane was reported missing.
Costa Rican and Panamanian planes and boats joined the Nicaraguan
forces.
